article.headline: IPFW 72, North Dakota St 64
article.story: FORT WAYNE, Ind. (AP) -- Quinton Carouthers and DeWitt Scott each scored 23 points to lead IPFW over North Dakota State 72-64 on Sunday. Carouthers also grabbed 10 rebounds for the Mastodons (9-18). He and Scott were the only players in double figures for IPFW, who went 12-for-12 at the free-throw line, all in the second half. Ben Woodside scored a game-high 24 points, including 8-of-10 from the line, to lead North Dakota State (16-22). Mike Nelson scored 16 for the Bison. Andre Smith had a double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds. IPFW led 35-31 at the break. The Mastodons outshot the Bison 50.9 percent to 44.2 percent overall.
